{
  "stem": "1918.5",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's-- it's not possible to hand down the experience to the-- to the exact [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] shape of the way it really was because you simply-- you-- you just had to be there to know what it was like.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] You know, when we see films and all kinds of plays, we don't hear ourselves talk.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Who speaks for us?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The most important people in the drama are the prisoners.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The most important actors in the drama are the prisoners, who were-- who were-- who can't-- they're the only ones who can pry open the inside of a person who was Hitler's prisoner.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nobody else can speak for them, somehow.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Try, they do.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and there are eloquent writings, introductions, and everything, but [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] who can lay the soul bare of the person who was the person.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After Auschwitz, we didn't-- we tried, in a sense, to stay in Auschwitz because getting away from Auschwitz meant that you had to be selected by Mengele.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we couldn't afford the selection because there were four of us, and he could select us in four different directions.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One to another camp, one to the crematorium, one to yet another camp, one to remain in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we couldn't afford.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we had to run as fast as we could.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "One night, we ran as he was selecting.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we ran out the back door.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he came after us, and he shot.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he missed us in the dark.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He-- he missed all four of us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But we ran even at the possibility of being shot because it's better to be shot together than live alone.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because that was the only meaning to our existence, is to be together.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
